Dear Jacobo Aragunde P=C3=A9rez,

I see that you have been added to the POI PMC. Congratulations!

As a PMC member, you=E2=80=99re entrusted with the direction of the =
project, as well as its ongoing relationship with the Board and the rest =
of the Foundation, so we wanted to welcome you to the larger ASF family.

And in the same way that you have been added to the PMC by others, =
remember that part of your duty is now to be the one to be on the =
lookout for other potential committers and PMC members for your project, =
and to mentor those people into project leadership, to ensure the =
sustainability of your project, and of the Foundation.

We=E2=80=99ve put together some resources for PMC members at =
https://community.apache.org/pmc/ That=E2=80=99s still a work in =
progress and we hope it will improve over time. We=E2=80=99d like to =
hear your feedback on how this resource could be improved, based on =
information that you learn and wish someone had told you.

If you have any questions about any aspect of the Foundation, or want to =
chat about how the Foundation can better serve your project, please =
reach out to myself, or to the Community Development list at =
dev@community.apache.org <mailto:dev@community.apache.org>=20

Rich, on behalf of the Community Development PMC.




