It=E2=80=99s exciting to hear from you, and about your event. =
Unfortunately, we do not, at this time, have budget to support events of =
this nature - as much as I would like to. What we can do is help =
publicize your event, which might potentially bring sponsorships. Can =
you provide a link to a website or invite link that we can get the word =
out on?

=E2=80=94Rich

> On Jun 29, 2026, at 6:19=E2=80=AFPM, Narcisse Mbunzama =
<mbunzama@gmail.com> wrote:
>=20
> Dear Apache Software Foundation Committee,
>=20
> I hope this message finds you well.
>=20
> I am writing to request support for organizing *Apache Meetup Kinshasa =
2026*
> in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC).
>=20
> Apache Meetup Kinshasa 2026 is a community-driven technical event =
focused
> on open-source software development, distributed systems, and modern
> backend engineering within the Apache ecosystem. The initiative aims =
to
> strengthen local capacity in open-source technologies and foster =
active
> participation in global Apache projects. It will bring together =
software
> developers, students, engineers, researchers, educators, and =
technology
> enthusiasts in Kinshasa who are interested in scalable systems, cloud
> infrastructure, and open-source collaboration.
>=20
> Scheduled for *July 20, 2026*, in Kinshasa, the meetup is designed to
> provide a collaborative environment where participants can enhance
> technical skills, share knowledge, and build long-term professional =
and
> community connections within the Apache and broader open-source =
ecosystem.
> Objectives
>=20
> The meetup is designed to:
>=20
>   - Promote awareness and adoption of Apache projects and open-source
>   technologies in the Congolese technology ecosystem;
>   - Strengthen practical skills in distributed systems, backend
>   engineering, and cloud-native architectures;
>   - Encourage contribution to Apache Software Foundation projects and
>   global open-source communities;
>   - Support capacity building through workshops, technical sessions, =
and
>   peer learning;
>   - Foster inclusive participation in open-source development across =
the
>   DRC;
>   - Establish a sustainable local community around Apache technologies =
in
>   Kinshasa.
>=20
> Meetup Activities
>=20
> The program will include a combination of technical and =
community-focused
> activities, including:
>=20
>   - Introductory and intermediate sessions on Apache ecosystem =
projects
>   and tools;
>   - Talks on distributed systems, scalability, and backend =
architecture;
>   - Demonstrations of Apache technologies in real-world applications =
(data
>   processing, cloud infrastructure, and web services);
>   - Hands-on workshops and collaborative coding sessions;
>   - Guidance on contributing to Apache open-source projects;
>   - Networking sessions for developers, students, educators, and =
industry
>   professionals;
>   - Community discussions on long-term engagement with open-source
>   ecosystems.
>=20
> Target Audience
>=20
> The meetup is intended for approximately *50 participants*, including:
>=20
>   - Software developers and backend engineers;
>   - University students and recent graduates;
>   - Systems and cloud infrastructure engineers;
>   - Open-source contributors and Linux enthusiasts;
>   - Technology educators and researchers;
>   - Startup founders and software entrepreneurs;
>   - Individuals interested in distributed systems and open-source
>   development.
>=20
> Expected Impact
>=20
> Apache Meetup Kinshasa 2026 aims to contribute to the growth of a =
stronger
> and more connected open-source ecosystem in the Democratic Republic of =
the
> Congo. The initiative is expected to:
>=20
>   - Increase awareness and adoption of Apache technologies and =
open-source
>   software;
>   - Expand access to technical education in distributed systems and
>   backend engineering;
>   - Support the development of local mentorship and collaborative =
learning
>   networks;
>   - Encourage participation of Congolese developers in global Apache
>   projects;
>   - Create long-term opportunities for innovation and open-source
>   contribution.
>=20
> Event Information
>=20
> *Event Name:* Apache Meetup Kinshasa 2026
> *Date:* July 20, 2026
> *Location:* Kinshasa, Democratic Republic of the Congo
> *Format:* In-person community meetup and workshop
> *Expected Attendance:* Approximately 50 participants
> *Participation Fee:* Free of charge
> Funding and Support
>=20
> The total budget required for organizing Apache Meetup Kinshasa 2026 =
is *USD
> 1,500*.
>=20
> This funding will support venue logistics, internet connectivity,
> participant materials, communication and outreach, audiovisual =
equipment,
> refreshments, volunteer coordination, and other essential operational =
costs
> required to deliver a successful community event.
>=20
> Additional support in the form of mentorship, technical guidance,
> educational resources, and visibility within the Apache ecosystem =
would
> significantly enhance the impact and sustainability of this =
initiative.
> Organizer
>=20
> Narcisse Mbunzama is a software developer, trainer, and technology
> community leader from the Democratic Republic of the Congo. He holds a
> Master=E2=80=99s degree in Computer Science and has more than six =
years of
> experience leading developer education and community initiatives as =
Lead of
> the DRC Developer Association. His work focuses on software =
engineering,
