> Hi Kshitij,
> Thanks for reaching out, please find the response inline below
> >   1.
> >   When the application portal for the next GSoC program is expected to
> >   open.
>
> The next GSoC program is expected to start around March 2027, keep
> checking the updates on the website.
>
> >   2.
> >   The recommended timeline for starting contributions before submitting=
 a
> >   proposal.
>
> You are welcome to contribute as and when you like, anytime is a good tim=
e
> to bond with the community, the sooner the better.
>
> >   3.
> >   Best practices for making meaningful open-source contributions that
> >   strengthen a GSoC application.
>
> Once you find a project idea that interests you, start contributing to th=
e
> respective project, interact with the community and try to understand wha=
t
> you can help with. For example this year's idea list
> https://s.apache.org/gsoc2026ideas
>
> >   4.
> >   Official resources or documentation that every prospective GSoC
> >   contributor should review.
>
> https://community.apache.org/gsoc/
>
> >   5.
> >   Whether contributors should contact organizations directly before the
> >   application period, and if so, the recommended way to do so.
>
> Yes, it is good to be active in the project community from the start so
> that you can get insights on your proposal. and better ways to contribute=
.
>
> I hope you find this contributor guide helpful
> https://community.apache.org/contributors/
>
>
