Hi dev@,

Following up on the budget discussion thread [1] and the earlier
"thinking bigger" conversation [2], I've drafted a proposed working
group structure for how event support and speaker travel grants could
actually work if we get budget approved.

Two PRs are up for review:

  https://github.com/apache/comdev-working-groups/pull/47
  https://github.com/apache/comdev-site/pull/233

The first (comdev-working-groups) adds wg-events/ with:

  - Charter and structural rules
  - Speaker travel grant process with a scoring rubric
  - Copy-paste email application forms for meetups, sprints,
    summits, and materials reimbursement
  - Evaluation criteria (scored 0-3 on 5 dimensions)
  - Private SVN data format for tracking grants
  - Committee operations howto
  - Helper scripts for maintaining the ledger

The second (comdev-site) adds shadow pages on community.apache.org
with the public-facing application forms and criteria. These pages
are not linked from anywhere yet -- they'll go live only if/when
budget is approved and the mailing list is created.

TO BE CLEAR: None of this is approved or active. There is no
mailing list, no budget, and no committee. This is just a proposal
for how the machinery could work.

I'm looking for feedback on:

  - Does the process make sense?
  - Is the scoring rubric reasonable?
  - Are there obvious gaps or failure modes?
  - Would you volunteer for the evaluation committee?

Discussion here on dev@. PRs are for the content itself -- if you
want to suggest specific wording changes, comment there.

--Rich

